e has more HPs than even our pets to and let him fight unaided like you do for the fight.  Watch his max hits, how much damage he takes from riposte, etc.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>The patch that changed resistance on the uber mobs also made a general change to resistances, but only for DDs.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote><BR>I'm sorry, but you are mistaken there.  It was even stated that they posted they were wrong initially.  All spell line resistances were lowered, proc, dd, dot, etc.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Maybe not 700 HP at each level, but atleast the same or maybe 100-200HP more than the last pet level.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote><BR>Allright, what would 200hps equate to?  2-3 more riposte hits considering the level gap inbetween the pet and your usual target. </P><P> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>As a high level Necromancer you should know that our Pets if used correctly our are most effiecient form of damage. How much mana did it cost you to cast all those DoTs? Now compare that to the cost of a pet and its damage output over and evening. <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>But these guys are all saying pets don't last a single fight, much less all night...I quoteth:<BR><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>...and thats cause there's usually 2 other things tanking for them. And even then, dmg shields or ripostes will kill them. <hr height=1 nosha