        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Am I the only person happy with necros as they are now?  I can honestly say I have no complaints with the necro class save for 2 bugs yet to be squished.  Pet lifetaps and Luclin spells not working.</P><P>I'm quite satisfied with our class otherwise.  I'm a jack of all trades, master of none.  A background groupmate.   Peeps don't even realize what we're doing for a raid and thats the way I like it.<BR>I'm not an expert mezzer but i can mez<BR>I'm not an expert healer but I can heal<BR>I'm not the fastest damager but I definitely contribute<BR>I'm not the best soloer but I'm good at it<BR>I have saved countless chanters hides<BR>It may not be much but my mana dumps do let clerics breathe a sigh of relief<BR>How loved am I when the only person left in the zone is a FD necro with an essence emerald in his pocket?<BR>Or when someone's corpse is sitting under Woushi's little toe?<BR>Hell I can even pull if need be.<BR>CR is a possibility even w/o coffins<BR>My pet isn't great on huge raids but he contributes too.  And if he's not around I've still got contributions to make.  He is *not* a tank, he's a manaless dot (almost).  It only seems fair that we have to keep an eye on him, not just summon him and throw him into the fray.  </P><P>We've got it all, why should we be masters of each skill too?  The only time I have a problem getting on a raid is when raid leaders don't understand what we're capable of.  Rah rah necros and all that jazz.  IMO we've got it about as good as it gets.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
